# Thin border enclosure protocol (v1.0.0)

Source of truth: `project/src/theme/themeThinBorderProtocol.ts`
Re-exported via: `buttonThemeService.ts`, `themeSurfaceStyles.ts`

## Mandatory rule (חוק מסגרת היקפית)

Whenever two structural layout containers share a visual boundary or are nested using identical/custom theme colors, wrap the **inner** element with a uniform **1px full-perimeter `border`** (not only `border-b`).

## CSS variables (auto-computed on theme change)

| Variable | Use |
|----------|-----|
| `--theme-enclosure-border` | Page-level / generic nested tint |
| `--main-card-surface-border` | Cat 6 master cards (alpha overlay from card bg) |
| `--color-sub-cards-border` | Cat 7 nested panels (alpha overlay from sub-card bg) |
| `--surface-input-border` | Cat 4 inputs inside bordered panels |

Dark surfaces → `rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12)` · Light surfaces → `rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.10)`

## Required tokens

- Cat 6 masters: `themeCardClass`, `themeCardLgClass` (include `border`)
- Cat 7 nested: `subCardClass`, `subCardSmClass`, `subCardAccordionShellClass`
- Nested stacks: `SubCardNestedStack` + `SubCardNestedItem` (`data-nested-list-enclosed`)
- Grid cells: `subCardGridCellClass`, `subCardGridCellIdleClass`

## Applies to

- Profile/Settings accordion section frames (מטבעות, הגדרות כלליות, עיצוב כפתורים)
- Dashboard month selector & financial summary inset panels
- Currency grid cards (ILS, USD, …) in מטבע תצוגה
- Chart/carousel insets (`filterInsetPanelClass`)

## Forbidden

- Nested Cat 7 blocks without a full `border` when inside Cat 6
- Hardcoded `border-gray-*` / `divide-neutral-*` for structural separation inside themed cards
- Replacing enclosure borders with shadow-only depth

## Cat 4 & Cat 1 inside bordered panels

Inputs use `surfaceInputClass` / `filterFormControlClass` (own `--surface-input-border`).
Buttons retain group tokens (`primaryActionButtonClass`, etc.) — do not remove their borders/rings.
